This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One. Gibbs provides updates on President Obama's visit to Louisiana to assess the oil spill situation. He explains that the President did not see any sign of the actual slick during the helicopter ride due to weather conditions. Gibbs also discusses the efforts being made to clean up the spill and the challenges faced in containing it. He mentions the need to set up a compensation system for affected fishermen and highlights the importance of state and local authorities working with the Coast Guard to respond to the oil slicks. Gibbs also addresses questions about the canceled trip to New Jersey, the government's dependence on BP, the President's frustration with the situation, and the comparison between the oil spill and Hurricane Katrina. He concludes by mentioning that the President is staying updated on the New York bomb plot investigation.